# 🧠 Prayog — High-Level Architecture Mental Model

---

## 1. SYSTEM OVERVIEW

**Prayog is an EdTech simulation platform** for learning income tax compliance.

Think of it as a "flight simulator for tax filing." Students read case studies (like a textbook), then practice filling out *a replica of the actual Indian Income Tax e-Filing portal* — and the system grades their work automatically.

### The Three Big Pillars

| Pillar | What It Does |
|---|---|
| **LMS (Learning Management System)** | Courses, programs, case studies — the "classroom" |
| **Simulation Engine** | A fake government portal where students practice filling forms |
| **Admin Panel** | For admins to manage users — the "back office" |

All three are gated behind **Supabase authentication** with **role-based access control** (admin vs. user).

---

## 2. FOLDER & ARCHITECTURE MENTAL MODEL

```
Prayog/
├── app/                    ← 🗺️ ROUTES (the map of your app)
│   ├── layout.tsx          ← Root shell: fonts, global providers
│   ├── login/              ← Auth gate
│   ├── (lms)/              ← 🎓 The "classroom" zone
│   │   ├── page.tsx        ← Homepage = Programs Dashboard
│   │   ├── offerings/      ← Browse new courses
│   │   ├── learning-contents/ ← Case study content
│   │   └── course/         ← Deep-dive into a course topic
│   ├── (simulation)/       ← 🧪 The "practice lab" zone
│   │   └── simulation/     ← Multi-step gov portal replica
│   ├── dashboard/          ← 🔒 Admin-only panel
│   └── api/                ← 🔌 Server-side API routes
│       └── admin/          ← User creation & listing endpoints
│
├── components/             ← 🧩 REUSABLE UI PIECES
│   ├── ui/                 ← Generic building blocks (Button, Card, Input…)
│   ├── lms/                ← LMS-specific components
│   ├── simulation/         ← Simulation-specific components
│   └── admin/              ← Admin-specific components
│
├── lib/                    ← 🔧 LOGIC & SERVICES (no UI here)
│   ├── supabase/           ← Auth & DB connection helpers
│   ├── simulation/         ← Registration state + constants
│   └── evaluation.ts       ← Auto-grading engine
│
├── hooks/                  ← 🪝 Custom React hooks
├── middleware.ts           ← 🚧 Auth gatekeeper (runs BEFORE pages)
└── public/                 ← Static assets (logos, images)
```

### How They Relate

```mermaid
graph TD
    MW["middleware.ts<br/>(Gatekeeper)"] --> LMS["(lms) Route Group<br/>The Classroom"]
